James Abraham, Jos The National Vice President of Academic Staff Union of Secondary Schools, Mr Adams Zakka Malau, has been killed by suspected gunmen. It was gathered on Tuesday that the union leader was shot dead at his residence in Ngoksar village, Bokkos Council Area of the State by the gunmen. One of the villagers who gave his name as Mandong Bitrus told our correspondent in Jos on Tuesday that the gunmen stormed the house of the union official around 7:30pm on Sunday and shot him dead. Bitrus said, “When we heard gunshots, we did not know what was happening as everybody was running in a different direction for safety. “After some minutes, when we did not hear any sound again, we returned only to find Malau in the pool of his own blood. The gunmen just shot him and disappeared. He died afterward.” Another villager, Gokyo who also confirmed the incident added that the gunmen also killed a 22-year-old man in neighboring Tangur village while trying to escape. According to him, the victim identified as Mr. Marvelous Yelwa was shot dead while running home after the gunmen had killed their first victim. The spokesman for the State Police Command, Mr. Mathias Typev, when contacted on Tuesday said he was on the entourage of the State Commissioner of Police, Mr Isaac Akinmoyede, who he said was on a tour of the council areas of the state. He promised to look into the matter upon his return to the command headquarters in Jos, the state capital.